    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3658" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπι-τρέχω</span></b> , aor. 1 part.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπιθρέξαντος</span>, aor. 2 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπέδραμον</span>, perf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐπιδέδρομα</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">run up, run upon</span>, often in
          hostile sense, <i><span class="en">Od. 14.30</span></i>; of horses
          putting forth their??peed, ‘ran <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">on</span>,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 23.418</span></i>, 447; the chariot rolling
          close <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">on</span> (behind) the horses, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.504</span></i>; a spear impinging upon a shield, <i><span class="en">Il. 13.409</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; λευκὴ δ᾽ ἐπιδέδρομεν αἴγλη</span>,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">runs over</span> all, <i><span class="en">Od.
            6.45</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἀχλύς</span>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            20.357</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
